<gap extent="1 line missing"/></p></lg>
<lg id="t.6.1.19.d7" type="proverb" n="19.d7"><p id="t6119.p24" n="10" corresp="c6119.D.19.d7.10">
<gap extent="1 line fragmentary"/></p></lg>
<lg id="t.6.1.19.d8" type="proverb" n="19.d8"><p id="t6119.p25" n="11" corresp="c6119.D.19.d8.11">
<note lang="eng">cf. <xref doc="t.6.2.5">6.2.5: IM 62823 Seg. B l. 4</xref></note>
<gap extent="1 line unclear"/></p></lg>
<lg id="t.6.1.19.d9" type="proverb" n="19.d9"><p id="t6119.p26" n="12" corresp="c6119.D.19.d9.12">
<note lang="eng">cf. <xref doc="t.6.1.03" from="t.6.1.03.41">6.1.03.41</xref>, <xref doc="t.6.1.28" from="t.6.1.28.25">6.1.28.25</xref></note>
When the mistress left the house and the slave girl entered from the street, away from her mistress the slave girl set up her own banquet.</p></lg>
<lg id="t.6.1.19.d10" type="proverb" n="19.d10"><p id="t6119.p27" n="13" corresp="c6119.D.19.d10.13">
<note lang="eng">cf. <xref doc="t.6.1.21" from="t.6.1.21.c7">6.1.21.c7</xref></note>
The litter was not apparent to the slave girl. To her mistress it just kept increasing.</p></lg>
<lg id="t.6.1.19.d11" type="proverb" n="19.d11"><p id="t6119.p28" n="14-15" corresp="c6119.D.19.d11.14">
<note lang="eng">cf. <xref doc="t.6.2.3" from="t623.h71">6.2.3: UET 6/2 386</xref>, <xref doc="t.6.2.3" from="t623.h72">6.2.3: UET 6/2 387</xref></note>
As a slave girl, I have no authority over my mistress. So let me pull at my husband's hair.
<gap extent="unknown no. of lines missing"/></p>
</lg></div1><div1 type="segment" n="E">
<lg id="t.6.1.19.e1" type="proverb" n="19.e1"><p id="t6119.p29" n="1" corresp="c6119.E.19.e1.1">
<gap extent="1 line fragmentary"/></p></lg>
<lg id="t.6.1.19.e2" type="proverb" n="19.e2"><p id="t6119.p30" n="2-3" corresp="c6119.E.19.e2.2">
<note lang="eng">cf. <xref doc="t.6.1.09" from="t.6.1.09.d2">6.1.09.d2</xref>, <xref doc="t.6.2.3">6.2.3: UET 6/3 464 ll. 1-2</xref></note>
The clever one &X;&X;. The wise one &X;&X;.</p></lg>
<lg id="t.6.1.19.e3" type="proverb" n="19.e3"><p id="t6119.p31" n="4-5" corresp="c6119.E.19.e3.4">
<note lang="eng">cf. <xref doc="t.6.1.09" from="t.6.1.09.d3">6.1.09.d3</xref>, <xref doc="t.6.1.13" from="t.6.1.13.29">6.1.13.29</xref>, <xref doc="t.6.2.3">6.2.3: UET 6/3 464 l. 3</xref></note>
A fool who was overwhelmed by his backside stuck his hand up his backside.</p></lg>
<lg id="t.6.1.19.e4" type="proverb" n="19.e4"><p id="t6119.p32" n="6-7" corresp="c6119.E.19.e4.6">
